1 unit Black Beans
1 teaspoon Hot Sauce
1 tablespoon Fajita Spice Blend
4 tablespoon Guacamole
1 cup Mexican Cheese Blend
1 unit Chicken Stock Concentrate
10 ounce Shrimp
6 unit Flour Tortillas
3 tablespoon Sour Cream
Salt
Pepper
Cooking Oil
Butter

• Open package of chicken* and drain off any excess liquid.
• Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
chicken in a single layer; season with half the Fajita Spice Blend
(you’ll use the rest in the next step), a pinch of salt, and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through,
4-6 minutes.
• Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Turn off heat;
transfer chicken to a plate. Wash out pan.

• While chicken cooks, drain and rinse beans.
• In a medium microwave-safe bowl, combine beans, stock
concentrate, remaining Fajita Spice Blend, 2 TBSP water, 1 TBSP
butter, 1⁄2 tsp salt, and pepper (4 TBSP water, 2 TBSP butter,
and 1 tsp salt for 4 servings). Cover tightly with plastic wrap and
microwave until beans are warmed through, 2-3 minutes.
• Mash about half the beans with a potato masher or fork. Taste
and season with salt and pepper if desired. TIP: If you added any
other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can
get started on them now!

• Arrange tortillas, chicken, beans, and Mexican cheese blend
family style for everyone to assemble their own quesadillas. TIP:
Place filling of your choice on one half of a tortilla; fold tortilla in
half over filling to form a quesadilla.
• Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat.
Add quesadillas and cook on one side until golden brown,
2-3 minutes.
• Carefully flip quesadillas; cook until golden brown and cheese
melts, 1-2 minutes more. TIP: Work in batches if needed, adding
another drizzle of oil between batches and reducing heat if
quesadillas start to brown too quickly.

• Halve quesadillas.
• Serve quesadillas with sour cream, guacamole, and hot sauce
on the side. (Don’t forget to serve with any extra items you may
have ordered to build out your meal!)

***Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.***